  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       GUARDIAN
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="doc-section" id="tr-guard">
    <h2>Guardian Utilities</h2>
    <p>
      Tibetan script has tall vowel marks (གི, གུ, གེ) and stacked consonants that get clipped by tight layouts. Guardian utilities fix these rendering issues.
    </p>

    <!-- .tr-guard -->
    <h3><code>.tr-guard</code></h3>
    <p>Adds vertical padding (<code>padding-block: 0.25em</code>) to prevent clipping of vowel marks and stacked consonants. Use on every Tibetan text element. For extra-large text, use <code>.tr-guard-lg</code> (<code>0.5em</code>).</p>
    <div class="compare-row">
      <div class="compare-col">
        <div class="compare-label bad">Without .tr-guard</div>
        <div style="background:#0f172a; padding:0.5rem 1rem; border-radius:6px; overflow:hidden; line-height:1.2;">
          <p class="tr-jomolhari" lang="bo" style="font-size:1.4rem; color:#e2e8f0; margin:0; line-height:1.2; padding:0;">རྒྱལ་བའི་བསྟན་པ་རིན་པོ་ཆེ།</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="compare-col">
        <div class="compare-label good">With .tr-guard</div>
        <div style="background:#0f172a; padding:0.5rem 1rem; border-radius:6px; overflow:hidden;">
          <p class="tr-jomolhari tr-guard" lang="bo" style="font-size:1.4rem; color:#e2e8f0; margin:0;">རྒྱལ་བའི་བསྟན་པ་རིན་པོ་ཆེ།</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="code-standalone">
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-block-header">
          <span class="code-block-title">HTML</span>
          <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
        </div>
        <pre><code><span class="tag">&lt;p</span> <span class="attr">class</span>=<span class="str">"tr-jomolhari <span class="hl">tr-guard</span>"</span> <span class="attr">lang</span>=<span class="str">"bo"</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span>རྒྱལ་བའི་བསྟན་པ་རིན་པོ་ཆེ།<span class="tag">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="cmt">&lt;!-- For headings / large text --&gt;</span>
<span class="tag">&lt;h1</span> <span class="attr">class</span>=<span class="str">"tr-jomolhari <span class="hl">tr-guard-lg</span>"</span> <span class="attr">lang</span>=<span class="str">"bo"</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span>...<span class="tag">&lt;/h1&gt;</span></code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-section" id="tr-overflow-safe">
    <h3><code>.tr-overflow-safe</code></h3>
    <p>Last-resort overflow protection for constrained containers. Prevents Tibetan text from spilling out of its box when no break opportunities exist.</p>
    <p><strong>Important:</strong> this is <em>not</em> tsheg-aware line breaking. It uses <code>overflow-wrap: anywhere</code> which breaks at byte boundaries — potentially mid-syllable — as a fallback. For correct line-breaking at tsheg, use <code>terma.prepare()</code> from <code>terma.js</code>.</p>
    <div class="code-standalone">
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-block-header">
          <span class="code-block-title">HTML</span>
          <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
        </div>
        <pre><code><span class="tag">&lt;div</span> <span class="attr">class</span>=<span class="str">"<span class="hl">tr-overflow-safe</span>"</span> <span class="attr">style</span>=<span class="str">"max-width: 300px"</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span>
  <span class="tag">&lt;p</span> <span class="attr">class</span>=<span class="str">"tr-jomolhari tr-guard"</span> <span class="attr">lang</span>=<span class="str">"bo"</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span>
    བཅོམ་ལྡན་འདས་མ་ཤེས་རབ་ཀྱི་ཕ་རོལ་ཏུ་ཕྱིན་པའི་སྙིང་པོ།
  <span class="tag">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="tag">&lt;/div&gt;</span></code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-section" id="tr-scale-up">
    <!-- .tr-scale-up -->
    <h3><code>.tr-scale-up</code></h3>
    <p>Scales Tibetan text to <code>120%</code> to match the visual weight of surrounding English text. Use <code>.tr-scale-match</code> (<code>150%</code>) for headings or when Tibetan needs more presence.</p>
    <div class="compare-row">
